<% if calculator.due_date >= Date.parse("2026-04-05") && calculator.due_date <= Date.parse("2026-07-25") && calculator.employment_status_of_partner == "employee" && calculator.where_does_the_mother_partner_live != "northern_ireland" %>
  ##Paternity leave

  The mother’s partner can take up to 2 weeks' [paternity leave](/paternity-pay-leave/leave).

  Paternity leave must be used by <%= format_date(calculator.take_paternity_leave_by_date) %>.

  From 18 February 2026 until 25 July 2026, the partner does not need to give the usual 15 weeks' notice of their baby’s due date.

  The partner must still tell their employer by <%= format_date(calculator.give_paternity_leave_notice_by_date) %> when they want their leave to start.

<% elsif calculator.due_date > Date.parse("2026-07-25") && calculator.employment_status_of_partner == "employee" && calculator.partner_continuity? == false && calculator.where_does_the_mother_partner_live != "northern_ireland" %>
  ##Paternity leave

  The mother’s partner can take up to 2 weeks' [paternity leave](/paternity-pay-leave/leave).

  Paternity leave must be used by <%= format_date(calculator.take_paternity_leave_by_date) %>.

  The partner must tell their employer:

  - the baby’s due date - by <%= format_date(calculator.due_date_notice_to_partner_employer) %>
  - when they want their leave to start - by <%= format_date(calculator.give_paternity_leave_notice_by_date) %>

<% else %>
  ##Statutory Paternity Leave 

  The mother’s partner cannot take [Statutory Paternity Leave](/paternity-pay-leave/leave).

  ##Statutory Paternity Pay

  The mother’s partner cannot take [Statutory Paternity Pay](/paternity-pay-leave/pay).
<% end %>
